<%= erb :header %>
	<h1>Caesar Cipher</h1>
	<div class="msg-io left-text">
		<p>Caesar's cipher is a monoalphabetic substitution cipher. Each letter in the alphabet is replaced by a different letter based on a specific key.</p>
		<p>Text is encrypted by shifting the alphabet by this key number of spaces. So a Caesar shift of 3 would result in "a" becoming "d", "b" becoming "e", and so on.</p>
		<ul>
			<li class = "mono">Plain text: &nbsp;ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ</li>
			<li class = "mono">Cipher text: DEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZABC</li>
		</ul>
		<p>Using this shift of 3 "Meet me at the secret spot" would be encrypted to "Phhw ph dw wkh vhfuhw vsrw".</p>
		<p>Give it a try!</p>
	</div>
	<form id="caesar" method="post" action="/caesar">
		<div class="form-group">
			<label>Enter your secret message here!</label>
			<textarea name="encrypt" form= "caesar" class="form-control msg-io"></textarea>
		</div>
		<div class="form-group">
			<label>Key</label>
			<input type="number" name="shift" class="form-control msg-io" value="3">
		</div>
<%= erb :footer %>